              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Coupled Cyclotron Facility (CCF) projectile",
                "fragmentation facility at the National Superconducting",
                "Cyclotron Laboratory was used in conjunction with the",
                "ReA3 reaccelerator to produce beams of 46 K. The",
                "stable 39 K beams at the were produced using only the",
                "ReA3 facility."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Reconstruction of the velocity vectors of the",
                "coincident fragments allowed to calculate the",
                "masses and angular distributions of the fragments.",
                "Capture-fission excitation function can be taken as",
                "the capture excitation function because straight-",
                "forward calculations for these reactions indicate",
                "that 99% of the capture events undergo fission."
              ]
            }
